<p><strong>Ripple Crescent Halberd</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Halberds" href="/Halberds">Halberd</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Ripple Crescent Halberd</strong>&nbsp;scales&nbsp;solely with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane" target="">Arcane</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a>&nbsp;for any Arcane build with its decent range and flexible moveset, and is great for Arcane casters in need of a buffable weapon.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Weapon wielded by young Albinaurics.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The blade is said to resemble a partial image of a ripple, and its attack power scales with one's arcane attribute.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Ripple Crescent Halberd in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Ripple Crescent Halberd weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Has a low&nbsp;chance to drop from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Albinauric" href="/Albinauric">Albinaurics</a>&nbsp;that wields it, found in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Academy Gate Town" href="/Academy+Gate+Town">Academy Gate Town</a> 
  <ul> 
   <li>A group of three Albinaurics who wield this weapon can be found at&nbsp;the first&nbsp;ruin to the east of the <strong>Fallen Ruins of the Lake</strong>&nbsp;Site of Grace in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Liurnia" href="/Liurnia" target="">Liurnia</a> [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=5714&amp;lat=-146.837499&amp;lng=60.819587&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=5714&amp;lat=-146.837499&amp;lng=60.819587&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map Link</a>]. 
    <ul> 
     <li>Two Albinaurics can be found sitting&nbsp;at the southern end of the ruin. One can be found standing on top of the ruin.</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Drops fairly quickly near the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4614&amp;code=mapB" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4614&amp;code=mapB">Palace Approach Ledge-Road</a> grace. Just past the shoreline, there is a tree with half a dozen or so enemies carrying this halberd.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Ripple Crescent Halberd Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spinning Slash" href="/Spinning+Slash">Spinning Slash</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War">Ashes of War</a>, but <em>can</em> be buffed with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic">Magic</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li>This is one of few arcane scaling weapons that can be buffed, as arcane scaling increases status-effect buildup as well as damage, this is ideal for a melee arcane build that uses a lot of greases.</li> 
</ul> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Grease Statistics</strong> 
  <ul> 
   <li>Keep in mind that the only greases that scale with Arcane are: Blood Greases, Poison Greases, and Soporific Greases</li> 
   <li>Status Grease Build-Up with +25 Ripple Crescent Halberd and 45 Arcane: 
    <ul> 
     <li>Poison Grease - 177</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Poison Grease - 225</li> 
     <li>Blood Grease - 84</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Blood Grease - 107</li> 
     <li>Soporific Grease - 93</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Soporific Grease - 118</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
   <li>Status Grease Build-Up with +25 Ripple Crescent Halberd and 60 Arcane: 
    <ul> 
     <li>Poison Grease - 200</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Poison Grease - 254</li> 
     <li>Blood Grease - 94</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Blood Grease - 121</li> 
     <li>Soporific Grease - 105</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Soporific Grease - 133</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
   <li>Status Grease Build-Up with +25 Ripple Crescent Halberd and 80 Arcane: 
    <ul> 
     <li>Poison Grease - 208</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Poison Grease - 264</li> 
     <li>Blood Grease - 99</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Blood Grease - 125</li> 
     <li>Soporific Grease - 109</li> 
     <li>Drawstring Soporific Grease - 139</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>The <strong>Ripple Crescent Halberd</strong> has less Status Grease Build-Up the its axe counterpart, The <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ripple Blade" href="/Ripple+Blade">Ripple Blade</a>. However, the Ripple Crescent Halberd has significantly longer reach and an inherently superior moveset due to being a halberd. Also, in PvP, the extra Status Build-Up the Ripple Blade has over the Ripple Crescent Halberd is purely overkill since both weapons already proc Poison and Sleep in just two hits using their respective Drawstring Grease.</li> 
</ul> 
<ul> 
 <li>Spell buffs like Bloodflame blade don't appear to scale properly on this weapon, however.</li> 
 <li><strong>Ripple Crescent Halberd</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100</li> 
 <li>Base drop rate is 2% (at 100 Discovery)</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
