				<li id="16737838" class="cmnt-root" data="23" data-d="1657941288000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://fextralife.com/avatars/89580_1567712735.gif" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=89580" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">EvilUnicornLord</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579297/Ripple-Crescent-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">15 Jul 2022 23:14</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16737838" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Whenever a weapon has arcane scaling, it not only increases the damage, but also any status effect build-up on it. This and the ripple crescent axe are the only (I think) arcane scaling weapons that can be buffed.<br/><br/><br/>HOWEVER, spell buffs like bloodflame blade don&apos;t seem to function properly on them as it took about as long for me to bleed the mad troll outside volcano manor with this on 55 ARC as it did for me to bleed him with a banished knight halberd. Blood grease worked significantly better. So basically this is the ideal weapon for a melee arcane build that relies on greases instead of innate build-up but avoid using bloodflame blade, poison armament, frozen armament, etc. until they fix their functionality with this.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16737838" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#repli