				<li id="16700710" class="cmnt-root" data="-3" data-d="1653903934000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579297/Ripple-Crescent-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">30 May 2022 05:45</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16700710" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Hilarious weapon with greases, and ChasetheBro recently showcased how good it could be. I finally crash-tested this yesterday for great results -- and not only is the high status build alone good, but it also meshes with the Pulley Crossbow in the offhand for a full-on status build. Rot people, sleep them, bleed them, so many options -- Black Key bolts with a Rot Grease will rot people in a single barrage, Bleed grease and Barbed Bolts will deal over 60% of the bleed bar. The halb itself is still the main source of damage, don&apos;t spam the crossbow -- just having sleep grease on and poking deals over 40% of the sleep bar plus damage, while the crossbow can be partially poised and doesn&apos;t take advantage of phantom hits as well.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16700710" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16700710" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull