				<li id="16608704" class="cmnt-root" data="2" data-d="1649641691000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579297/Ripple-Crescent-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">10 Apr 2022 21:48</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16608704" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">So, I’ve changed my tune on these. Are there better halberds? Probably and definitely. However, these do happen to have a niche for arcane casters to squeeze out a few more stat points if they’re going for a certain level.<br/><br/><br/>It would be a non-bleed arcane build which is generally not meta, but in PvE, powerstancing these deals solid damage and the jumping R2 has some stagger power. Since Spinning Slash is kinda underwhelming and having no STR scaling means there’s no real reason to 2H it means using a buckler or using Golden Parry/Carian Retaliation are great options. Being a halberd, it has great reach. Keeping a catalyst in one hand, I like to cast Swarm of Flies on an enemy, then follow after it a jumping powerstance L1. Because of the high arcane stats with Dragon Communion Seal, the bleed is triggered quickly (at 63 arcane it was taking 4 hits of the cloud to proc it) and then you come slamming in with the halberds. I can one shot enemies in Farum at RL 125 because of this.<br/><br/><br/>It’s a slower style compared to powerstance dual seppuku weapons, but it’s safer as you have good reach, ranged bleed spell, and feel less punished to use a shield to address situations. Not dedicating as many points to STR/DEX like other weapons means a little more to INT/FTH.<br/><br/><br/>One downside: for buffing, you’ll need to use a different catalyst outside Albinauric and Dragon Communion. But otherwise, you can reach solid AR from elemental buffs due to scorpion charms and tears.<br/><br/><br/>So, it can be surprisingly versatile as other occult halberd/scythes either require some quality to work or locks you into a non-buffable bleed.<br/><br/><br/>While not meta, it definitely stands on its own with the right build.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16608704" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16608704" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16608704"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16608704" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16608704"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
