				<li id="16554254" class="cmnt-root" data="61" data-d="1647941933000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579297/Ripple-Crescent-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">22 Mar 2022 05:38</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16554254" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Just a heads up, the value of this weapon isn&apos;t in its standard attack rating. It does low damage on its own. It&apos;s valuable because it&apos;s S-tier Arcane scaling *that can be enchanted*. You can stack Bloodflame Blade on this.<br/><br/>...and the downside to that is that the Arcane-scaling seals are still bugged (as of 1.03) to not account for Arcane and only account for Faith, so you don&apos;t really see any bonus from that. But once they fix that bug, max arcane, slap Bloodflame Blade on this for buffed up bleed and an extra ~150 fire damage, and you&apos;ve got a pretty rad weapon.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16554254" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16554254" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">4</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>61</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="su